                    <span>Upon  reading  "My  American  Journey," I  felt  an  enourmous  sense  of  pride  for  the  United  States  of  America.  Secretary  Powell  is  an  example  of  what  people  can  be  become  through  hard  work  and  determination.  In  his  autobiagraphy, Powell  allows  the  reader  to  become  aware  of  the  challenges  this  country  has  endured  and  how  he  has  over  come  obsticles  that  have  been  placed  throughout  his  life.<br>     Powell  lets  the  reader  become  aware  of  where  he  stands  on  various  important  issues  that  have  been  part  of  both  United  States  international  and  domestic  policy.  Even  if  one  does  not  agree  with  him  politically, we  can  all  gain  from  his  sense  of  respect  and  devotion  to  ones  country.  This  is  a  must  read  for  any  one  interested  in  the  life  of  a  great  American  hero.</span>
                  
              
